Working with CQ for a while now me and other users struggle again and again with the fact that CQ is not as close to Confluence as it could be. Some ideas how to improve this:
 * In the CQ topics view {{questions/topics}} merge existing labels and make it easy to also make it a CQ topic
 * In the single topic view {{/questions/topics/%topicid%/%topicname%}} add a link to the respective label view {{/label/%labelname%}}
 * When entering new questions make labels also part of the proposal list
 * When entering labels for pages etc. make CQ topics part of the proposal list
 * Show CQ content in label content views {{/label/%spaceid%/%labelname%}} and {{/label/%labelname%}}
 * Show CQ topics in label navigation views {{/labels/listlabels-heatmap.action?key=%spaceid%}}, {{/labels/listlabels-heatmap.action}}, {{/labels/listlabels-alphaview.action?key=%spaceid%}}, {{/labels/listlabels-alphaview.action}}

Basic idea: Let information flow, use a common taxonomy. Don't create new user barriers just because you've decided to make this a separate plugin/team.

btw: Could not add this to the CQ project.
